      <explanation>Cleaner burning fuel.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Equivalent mass of FeC2O4 undergoing oxidation (Fe+2 to +3 AND C2O4 to CO2) is ____.</text>
      <option id="A">M / 3</option>
      <option id="B">M / 1</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Fe (+1 e-) + C2O4 (+2 e-) = 3 electrons total.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Sample space size for 3 coins:</text>
      <option id="A">8</option>
      <option id="B">6</option>
      <option id="C">3</option>
      <option id="D">9</option>
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Repeated.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Tollen's reagent is an ____ solution of silver nitrate.</text>
      <option id="A">Ammoniacal</option>
      <option id="B">Acidic</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Forms silver mirror with aldehydes.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Relation P = 1/3 n m v_rms^2 : 'n' is ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Number density (N/V)</option>
      <option id="B">Moles</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Molecules per unit volume.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Ksp for Ag2CrO4 is proportional to ____ cube of solubility s.</text>
      <option id="A">4 (Ksp = 4s^3)</option>
      <option id="B">1</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Salt formula A2B.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>The diagonal elements of a square matrix A = [a_ij] are elements for which ____.</text>
      <option id="A">i = j</option>
      <option id="B">i &gt; j</option>
      <option id="C">i &lt; j</option>
      <option id="D">i + j = n</option>
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Principal diagonal definition.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Two SHMs x1 = A sin wt and x2 = A cos wt have phase diff ____.</text>
      <option id="A">pi / 2</option>
      <option id="B">0</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Cosine is shifted sine.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>In SN2 reaction, the geometry of product is ____ with respect to reactant.</text>
      <option id="A">Inverted (Walden Inversion)</option>
      <option id="B">Retained</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Backside attack by nucleophile.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Kirchhoff's Law of Radiation: a_λ = ____.</text>
      <option id="A">e_λ (Absorptivity = Emissivity)</option>
      <option id="B">1 - e_λ</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Good absorbers are good emitters.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Physical quantities are those which can be ____.</text>
      <option id="A">Measured</option>
      <option id="B">Heard only</option>
      <option id="C">Imagined</option>
      
      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Standard definition.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>AgCl dissolves in NH4OH due to formation of ____ complex.</text>
      <option id="A">[Ag(NH3)2]Cl</option>
      <option id="B">[AgCl2]-</option>

      <answer>A</answer>
      <explanation>Soluble diammine silver(I) chloride.</explanation>
    </question>
    <question>
      <text>Slope of line 3x + 4y + 5 = 0:</text>
      <option id="A">-3/4</option>
      <option id="B">3/4</option>
      <option id="C">-4/3</option>
      <option id="D">4/3</option>
      <answer>A</answer>
